																		                    Pursuant to the Public Records Act (California Government Code (G.C.) Section 6250, et seq.), a person may request to review and/or receive a copy of any public record. While there are certain records exempt by statute (G.C. 6254), records of the City are public.There is no charge to review public records, however there are fees associated with obtaining copies of records. The fees are established in the Master Fee Schedule and vary depending upon the type of record and the method in which the record is provided. Whenever possible the City will provide the records electronically.It is not always feasible to provide an immediate copy for review or duplication, however the City strives to provide requested records within 10 days, or the requestor will be notified within 10 of when the record(s) may be available.For Police Department records, please visit Records Bureau Page for instructions.Name (First, Last)HankEmail Address (required to receive records electronically)199390-73349700@requests.muckrock.comPhone Number6172991832Preferred Method of ContactEmailAddress1MuckRock News, DEPT MR199390Address2263 Huntington AveCityBostonStateMassachusettsZip02115DepartmentsUnknownRecords RequestedTo Whom It May Concern:Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:1. Documents sufficient to show all user accounts for the department’s Flock deployment that were active between 3/29/2023 and the date that this request is processed.Documents that show who has access to the department’s Flock deployment and the access that is enabled/disabled for all user accounts (current and previously suspended, revoked, terminated, dormant, etc.). The report should include all available details including, but not limited to, the following where available: User ID, First Name, Last Name, Title, Role, Status, Identity Provider, Last login, User Mgmt, Search, Device Mgmt, Hotlist Tool.Records related to the department’s Flock Safety system:2. Organization Audit in Flock.The report should include data logged from the period of March 29, 2023, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Organization Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches done within the agency.3. Network Audit in Flock.The report should include data logged from the period of March 29, 2023, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Network Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches of the organization’s Flock network by any agency in the Flock System.4. A list of network share settings that include:4a. Networks that I’m sharing -The names of agencies and organizations with which the Agency shares its Flock Safety ALPR data, also referred to as "Networks that I’m sharing."4b. Flock networks shared with me -The names of agencies and organizations that have shared their cameras with the Agency, also referred to as "Flock networks shared with me."5. Any Non‑email records covering Flock Safety training presentations, published procedures, directives, training materials, promotional materials, or legal guidance.Please provide all responsive records in their original electronic and machine readable format. This includes, but is not limited to, spreadsheet files such as CSV or Excel, slide presentation files such as PowerPoint, and any other original native file formats. Please do not substitute scanned images or PDFs for original files, and please do not direct me to your transparency portal in place of providing the records.The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.Sincerely,HankUpload documents directly: https://www.muckrock.com/respond/2149697/
